  "title": "Electrical Engineer [SL]",
  "description": "<p><ul><li>Demonstrate strong site problem-solving and coordination skills to clients.</li><li>Particularly in design and compliance with building services codes of practice.</li><li>Ensure materials and installations by suppliers and subcontractors comply with the ISO quality plan.</li><li>Coordinate, monitor, and control suppliers’ materials, equipment, and subcontractor installation quality.</li><li>Prepare shop drawings and manage drawing coordination.</li><li>Develop work schedules and attend client and internal meetings.</li><li>Assist the Manager in daily site operations in accordance with master planning, quality, and safety requirements.</li><li>Maintain close coordination with the main contractor to minimize rework.</li><li>Control site materials and equipment to reduce wastage.</li><li>Communicate closely with suppliers and subcontractors to minimize delivery delays affecting progress.</li><li>Inspect materials and installations to identify and prevent non-conformance and defects.</li><li>Explore new technologies and installation methods to enhance productivity.</li><li>Monitor site progress closely and ensure clear communication with suppliers and subcontractors.</li></ul><p>Requirement</p></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li> Preferable 3-5 years relevant experience.</li></ul><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
